The linear moments technique was developed by Hosking (1990) to estimate parameters for extreme value probability distributions. This technique is at the core of the Flood Estimation Handbook's (FEH) statistical method to evaluate flood frequency-magnitude curves using recorded annual maximum flow data.

"lmoments3" is a Python programming library for use in academic research (e.g. application to national datasets) or integration into other software. The library is based on original Fortran code developed by Hosking (IBM, xxxx) and was originally converted into Python by Gillespie (xxxx). OH contributors further optimised the code and integrated this with widely used libraries "numpy" and "scipy".
